You are working on Routex, a multi-chain settlement cost router for the x402 payment protocol. It routes AI agent micropayments across Base, Polygon, Stellar, and Solana.

# Critical Rules

1. NEVER access .privateKey, .secretKey, or .mnemonic. Routex is non-custodial. Use the Signer interface — call .sign() or .signTypedData() only.

2. ALL token amounts must be bigint. Never use Number, parseFloat, or parseInt for monetary values. Use bigint literals (1000n) and BigInt arithmetic.

3. Each route() call must be stateless. No mutable module-level state. No singletons.

4. Never throw raw Error or strings. Use typed error classes from packages/core/src/errors.ts.

5. Strict TypeScript: strict: true, zero any in public API, no @ts-ignore.

6. Never swallow errors silently. Throw typed errors with context for graceful degradation.

# Code Style

- Single quotes, semicolons, 100 char width, trailing commas
- PascalCase for types/classes, camelCase for functions/vars, UPPER_SNAKE for constants
- async/await only, never .then() chains
- readonly on interface fields, as const for literals
- Single index.ts barrel export per package
- Mark security paths with invariant IDs: // INV-2: recipient must match 402 requirement
- Mark BigInt operations: // BigInt: token amounts must never use floating point

# Error Messages

Include: chain name, public address, amount, error code
Exclude: signer objects, credentials, RPC keys, private keys

# Architecture

- Monorepo: pnpm workspaces, tsup (dual CJS/ESM), vitest
- 5-step routing pipeline: parse → filter → score → select → verify
- Strategy functions are pure: (RouteOption[]) => RouteOption[]
- Promise.allSettled for parallel multi-chain queries
- Factory pattern: createRouter(), createBaseAdapter(), etc.

# Packages

- @routexcc/core — router engine, types, strategies, oracle, balance manager
- @routexcc/chain-base — Base L2 adapter (EVM, viem) + shared EvmAdapter
- @routexcc/chain-polygon — Polygon adapter (extends EvmAdapter)
- @routexcc/chain-stellar — Stellar adapter
- @routexcc/chain-solana — Solana adapter
- @routexcc/x402 — x402 middleware wrapper
- @routexcc/cloud — cloud fee oracle, telemetry, batch client
- @routexcc/test-utils — shared mocks and fixtures (private)

# Security Invariants

INV-1: No private key access
INV-2: Recipient matches 402 payTo
INV-3: Amount matches 402 requirement (BigInt)
INV-4: Chain ID matches selected adapter
INV-5: No silent failure (RouteExhaustedError)
INV-6: Stale fees rejected (maxFeeAgeMs)
INV-7: BigInt-only token arithmetic
INV-8: No credentials in error messages
INV-9: Stateless routing
INV-10: Graceful degradation

# Testing

- vitest, >= 90% coverage per package
- test/*.test.ts mirroring src/ structure
- Mock RPC calls, no live network
- Shared fixtures in packages/test-utils/

# Build Commands

pnpm install && pnpm build && pnpm test && pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck
